This module provides utilities for initializing and accessing the Firebase Admin SDK, allowing server-side access to Firebase services like Firestore.

## Key Exports

*   **`getAdminApp()`**: Initializes and returns the Firebase Admin `App` instance. It checks if an app has already been initialized and returns the existing one if available. Otherwise, it initializes a new app using credentials from environment variables (`FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`, `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL`, `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY`).
*   **`getAdminDb()`**: Returns a singleton instance of the Firestore database client. It leverages `getAdminApp()` to get the Firebase app and initializes Firestore if it hasn't been already.

## Usage

This module is intended to be used within a server-side environment where Firebase Admin SDK credentials are set as environment variables.

```typescript
import { getAdminDb } from "../lib/firebase-admin";

async function getUserData(userId: string) {
  const db = getAdminDb();
  const userDoc = await db.collection("users").doc(userId).get();
  if (!userDoc.exists) {
    console.log("No such document!");
    return null;
  } else {
    return userDoc.data();
  }
}
```
